  "issue_title": "[Bug] gitt miner post/check error path discards excluded validator list when --min-stake / --min-vtrust filters eliminate all candidates",
  "issue_body": "# Description:\n## Bug\n`gitt miner post` and `gitt miner check` both call `_require_validator_axons(...)`, which already returns an `excluded` list explaining *why* each high-vtrust validator was filtered (e.g. `stake 5,000 \u03b1 below 15,000 \u03b1 threshold`, `not serving an axon`). The **success path** uses this \u2014 it renders a `Skipped Validators` table in TTY mode and includes a `skipped` field in the JSON envelope. The **error path** discards `excluded` entirely and emits the generic message `\"No reachable validator axons found on the network.\"`, even when the real cause is the operator's `--min-stake` / `--min-vtrust` filter eliminating every candidate.\n\n## Source\n\n[`gittensor/cli/miner_commands/helpers.py:127-141`](https://github.com/entrius/gittensor/blob/test/gittensor/cli/miner_commands/helpers.py#L127-L141):\n\n```python\ndef _require_validator_axons(metagraph, json_mode, *, min_vtrust=..., min_stake=...):\n    validator_axons, validator_uids, excluded = _get_validator_axons(\n        metagraph, min_vtrust=min_vtrust, min_stake=min_stake\n    )\n    if not validator_axons:\n        _error('No reachable validator axons found on the network.', json_mode)  # \u2190 excluded discarded\n        sys.exit(1)\n    return validator_axons, validator_uids, excluded\n```\n\n## Reproduction\n\nNetwork with three high-vtrust validators (vtrust 0.99 / 0.85 / 0.72), all carrying stakes below the default `--min-stake=15000`:\n\n```\n$ gitt miner post --pat ghp_xxx --wallet alice --hotkey default\nError: No reachable validator axons found on the network.\n```\n\nSame in JSON mode \u2014 three known-but-skipped validators, each with explanation, are not surfaced:\n\n```json\n{\"success\": false, \"error\": \"No reachable validator axons found on the network.\"}\n```\n\nThe success path of the same command always emits a `skipped` array and prints the `Skipped Validators` table; the error path silently drops it.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nWhen all candidates are excluded by `--min-stake` / `--min-vtrust`:\n\n1. **TTY**: print the existing `Skipped Validators` table (already implemented in `_render_skipped_validators`) before the error, and use an actionable message like `No validators passed --min-vtrust=0.25 / --min-stake=15,000 \u03b1; all 3 candidate(s) excluded.`\n2. **JSON**: include the `skipped` array on the error envelope so JSON consumers see why the broadcast was empty.\n\nWhen the underlying metagraph is genuinely empty (no excluded UIDs either), keep the current generic message.\n\n## Affected commands\n\nBoth `gitt miner post` and `gitt miner check` go through `_require_validator_axons`.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-09T18:40:00.000Z",
